description:
The Israelites were God's chosen, beloved and blessed people. Of the eight privileges granted to them, one stood highest of all. The Bible identifies the chief privilege in Romans 3:2, the privilege of being keepers of the law of God, which is the very expression of His will. There are many important things we can learn from God's law. Learn why living in obedience to God's law is a privilege and why it is essential today for those who claim to be children of God (spiritual Israelites), through faith in Christ. 

Discover more: 
http://amazingdiscoveries.org
http://amazingdiscoveries.tv/media/1264/855-the-best-of-everything/
